      "eligibilityCriteria": {
        "eligibilityDescription_md": "\n1. The student and his parents should belong to the Brahmin community.\n1. The parents of the student should reside in Andhra Pradesh. \n1. The student&#39;s age should be between 8 to 19 years. \n1. The student should be pursuing a full-time vedic course (Yajur Veda, Rig Veda, Sama Veda, Atharvana Veda, or Smartham) in any of the Veda Pathasala registered with Tirumala Tirupati Devasthanams (TTD) or Endowments Department of Govt. of Andhra Pradesh or enlisted by the A.P. Brahmin Welfare Corporation.  \n1. The student applying for Padam, Kramam, Jata, and Ghanam should have completed their previous course of study.  \n1. The student should be enrolled in the Praja Sadhikara Survey (PSS).  \n\n<br>\n\n",
